Speech to Text: For many days, it has been happening on my lips every day. Every day, I have such scars on my lips. What should I do?
Doctor's Response: With what I see, I think you have a severe case of acne on your face, particularly on your lips and cheeks, which could be caused by a combination of factors such as hormonal imbalance, stress, or bacterial infection. To treat this, I would recommend using topical creams or gels containing salicylic acid or benzoyl peroxide to reduce inflammation and prevent further breakouts, and also consider consulting a dermatologist for further evaluation and possible prescription medication to help clear up your skin.
